<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Arsenal's hopes of signing Thomas Partey could be boosted by Atletico Madrid's interest in Lucas Torreira.</p>

<p>The Gunners have been heavily linked with a move for Partey throughout the transfer window as they look to strengthen their resources in midfield.</p>

<p>According to El Gol Digital, Atletico manager Diego Simeone rates Torreira highly.</p>

<p>Atletico Madrid could be willing to let Thomas Partey leave in a deal involving Lucas Torreira</p>

<p>The report indicates that Arsenal could offer Torreira to Atletico as part of a cash-plus-player deal.</p>

<p>Torreira has yet to play for Arsenal this season and has struggled to work his way back into the team since recovering from injury towards the end of last season. </p>

<p>Arsenal have so far been unwilling to match Atletico's demands of paying Partey's £45million release clause. </p>

<p>Atletico Madrid are interested in Torreira, who has fallen down the Arsenal pecking order</p>

<p>Atletico manager Diego Simeone rates Torreira very highly and could attempt to sign him</p>

<p>Ghana international Partey is said to be interested in making the move to Arsenal. </p>

<p>In addition to Partey, Arsenal have also been linked with a move for Lyon's Houssem Aouar, with Mikel Arteta's side certainly in need of extra creativity in midfield.</p>

<p>So far in this transfer window Arsenal have brought in Willian, Gabriel Magalhaes and Alex Runarsson, while Dani Ceballos returned on loan from Real Madrid.  </p>
